I ordered the pulled pork sandwich.
My wife ordered the 3 meat platter mostly so we could both have some ribs.
Pulled pork and brisket were the other meats on her plate.
She got the mac and cheese for a side, and I got the french fries.
It only took a few minutes for the food to arrive.
I thought the pulled pork was delicious.
My wife said the brisket was very good, though she's had better.
Not to say it was bad.
It was still very good.
We both loved the ribs.
The bottled BBQ sauce at the table was also made by one of the owners of the restaurant.
Both the sweet and spicy were really good.
I always look at the ingredients, and I was happy to see no high fructose corn syrup in them.
On a side note, we happened to be there when the wine sales woman was there.
My wife jokingly made a comment that if they needed any help sampling, we'd be more than happy to lend a taste bud or two.
Lucky for us, they took her up on the offer and we sampled three different wines.
Hopefully our critique of them helped to make a decision.
We will be back.

Excellent food and service.
Especially enjoyed the pulled pork with some spicy barbeque sauce.
They have made an effort to make the sides more interesting than those at most BBQ places and it definitely paid off.

